				3rd party partners such as
Booking.com
’s
privacy
				statement govern their handling of your information; our Privacy Notice does not govern the hotels’ privacy
				practices.
Service Providers
.  We may employ third party service providers to perform services on our behalf such as,
				couriers or shippers, credit card processors, marketing or research providers, web hosting and email service providers, and other data processors.
Online Advertising Partners
. We may also share personal data with advertising networks or permit these partners to
				collect information from you directly on our websites to facilitate online advertising, such as search engines and social network advertising providers to serve targeted ads to you or
				to groups of other users who share similar traits, such as likely commercial interests and demographics, on third-party platforms.  For more information, including how to opt out
				of interest-based advertising, please see our Cookie Notice.
Other Users of Our Services and The Public
.  We may provide functionality that enables you to disclose personal
				data to other users of Tablet or the public.  For instance, you may maintain a user profile with information about yourself that you can make available to other users or the
				public.  You may also be able to submit content to Tablet (such as comments, reviews, and photos), and we will display your name, username, and a link to your user profile along
				with the content you submit.
Professional Advisors
.  We may disclose your personal data to professional advisors, such as lawyers, bankers,
				auditors and insurers, in the connection with the professional services that they render.
For Compliance, Fraud Prevention and Safety
.  We may share your personal data for the compliance, fraud
				prevention and safety purposes described above.
Business Transaction or Reorganization
.  We may disclose or transfer your personal data in connection with or
				during the negotiation of a financing, merger, acquisition, dissolution or similar corporate event, or the sale of all or some of Tablet’s assets. The information that Tablet has
				collected, including personal data may be transferred as a business asset. Personal data may also be disclosed in the event of insolvency, bankruptcy, or receivership, in compliance
				with applicable law.
Legal Obligations or Rights
.  We may disclose personal data to third parties, such as legal advisors and law
				enforcement:
in connection with the establishment, exercise, or defense of legal claims;
to comply with laws or to respond to lawful requests and legal process;
to protect the rights and property of Tablet, our agents, customers, and others, including to enforce our agreements, notices, and our Terms
				of Use;
to detect, suppress, or prevent fraud;
to reduce credit risk and collect debts owed to us;
to protect the health and safety of us, our customers, or any person; or
as otherwise required by applicable law.
With Your Consent or At Your Direction
. We may disclose personal data about you to certain other third parties with
				your consent or at your direction.
4. Choices and Control Over Your Data
Depending on the jurisdiction in which you are located, you may be able to submit the following requests:
Access and Amend Your Information
.  You can access your personal data in your account.  You can change at
				any time your preferences for receiving or not receiving our emails and e-newsletters.  If you wish to modify your personal data or close your account, you can do so by contacting
				us as indicated in the “Contact Information” section below.  Once your account is closed, however, you will not be able to use many of the services available on our
				websites and mobile applications, unless you re-register.
Cookies and Browser Web Storage
.  We may allow service providers and other third parties to use cookies and
				similar technologies to track your browsing activity over time and across Tablet and third-party websites.  Please see our Cookie Notice for more information on the choices and
				controls you may have with cookies and similar technologies.
Targeted Online Advertising
.  Please refer to our Cookie Notice to learn more about how we work with third party
				partners to collect data through tracking technologies for various purposes, including analytics, advertising, and to understand your choices.
Opting Out of Marketing Communications
.  You may opt out of receiving marketing-related emails from us or change
				the volume of marketing-related emails you receive from us by following the update settings or unsubscribe instructions at the bottom of the email or by changing your preferences in
				the email preference center accessible through your account settings.  You may continue to receive service-related and other non-marketing emails from us.
Opting Out of Location Tracking
.  If you initially consented to the collection of geo-location information
				through the Tablet mobile application, you could subsequently stop the collection of this information at any time by changing the preferences on your mobile device.  Please note,
				however, that if you withdraw consent to Tablet’s collection of location information, you may no longer be able to use some Tablet features.
5. Third Parties
Tablet may contain links to other websites, mobile applications, and other online services operated by third parties.  These links are not an endorsement of,
			or representation that we are affiliated with, any third party.  Different rules may apply to other websites, mobile applications, or online services.  This Privacy Notice does
			not apply to, and we are not responsible for, any personal data practices of third-party websites and online services or the practices of other third parties. Tablet does not control the
			privacy notices of third parties.  We encourage you to review the privacy notices of the websites, mobile applications, or online services that you use or visit.
6. International Data Transfers
We are headquartered in the United States and have service providers in other countries, and your personal data may be transferred to the United States
			or other locations outside of your state, province, or country where privacy laws may not be as protective as those in your state, province, or country.
7. Children’s Personal Data
Tablet is not directed to, and we do not knowingly collect personal data from, anyone under the age of 16.  If we learn that we have collected personal
			data of a child under the age of 16, we will promptly delete such information.  If a child under the age of 16 has provided personal data to us, we encourage the child’s
			parent or guardian to contact us to request that we remove the personal data from our systems.
8. Updates To This Privacy Notice
We may amend this Privacy Notice at any time by posting the amended terms on this website.  In addition, we will notify you of material changes,
such
			as
			with an alert on the Tablet website or a communication to you via email (at the e-mail address specified in your account). All changes
			shall be effective from the date of publication unless otherwise provided.
